<p><em>please note this is not a duplicate, I'm looking for an updated answer.</em></p>  <p>I have been looking at a way of reducing repetitive code and was wondering if I could add multiple roles within the web config, within the one string.</p>  <p>From this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;location path="create.aspx"&gt;     &lt;system.web&gt;     &lt;authorization&gt;         &lt;allow roles="Admin"/&gt;         &lt;deny users="*"/&gt;     &lt;/authorization&gt;     &lt;/system.web&gt; &lt;/location&gt; &lt;location path="create.aspx"&gt;     &lt;system.web&gt;     &lt;authorization&gt;         &lt;allow roles="Member"/&gt;         &lt;deny users="*"/&gt;     &lt;/authorization&gt;     &lt;/system.web&gt; &lt;/location&gt; </code></pre>  <p>To something like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;location path="create.aspx"&gt;     &lt;system.web&gt;     &lt;authorization&gt;         &lt;allow roles="Admin,Member"/&gt;         &lt;deny users="*"/&gt;     &lt;/authorization&gt;     &lt;/system.web&gt; &lt;/location&gt; </code></pre>  <p>In this question <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2738394/requiring-multiple-roles-in-web-config-authorization">Requiring Multiple Roles in Web.config Authorization</a>  the answer is no.<br> But this is from 2010.<br> So I'm wondering if there has been a change to this since then?</p>  <p>Also, can the locations paths be added together?<br> In some fashion like so:  </p>  <pre><code>&lt;location path="create.aspx,delete.aspx"&gt; </code></pre>